He called
John Cooper
, a wheelwright, who had known him three years;
Benjamin Worthy
, who had known him twenty-one years;
David Mophet
the same; and
Richard Wilson
the same;
John Sutton
, sixteen;
Robert Webb
, fifteen;
Elizabeth
Mason, sixteen;
Thomas Harris
, five or six years; and
Richard Dolby
, six or seven weeks. They said he was a wheelwright , and of exceeding good character.
